question:
District category contains Learning Hub, Condo District, Wall Street, and Gated Community.
Supermarkets category contains Aldi (Germany), Bristol Farms, FreshDirect, and Hungryroot.
Product category contains Canned Tomatoes, Cupcakes, Wine, and Plant-based Yogurt.
The number of each Gated Community 's Aldi (Germany) equals 14 times each Aldi (Germany) 's Wine.
The number of each Bristol Farms 's Plant-based Yogurt equals 14.
The number of each Learning Hub 's Aldi (Germany) equals the sum of each Gated Community 's Product and each Aldi (Germany) 's Product.
The number of each Hungryroot 's Plant-based Yogurt equals each Learning Hub 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Learning Hub 's Bristol Farms equals 15 more than each Bristol Farms 's Plant-based Yogurt.
The number of each FreshDirect 's Cupcakes equals 17 more than each Condo District 's Hungryroot.
The number of each Aldi (Germany) 's Wine equals the difference of each FreshDirect 's Product and each FreshDirect 's Cupcakes.
The number of each Wall Street 's Hungryroot equals 11.
The number of each Condo District 's Hungryroot equals 13.
How many Aldi (Germany) does Learning Hub have?
solution:
Define each Condo District 's Hungryroot as t; So t = 13.
Define each FreshDirect 's Cupcakes as p; So p = 17 + t = 17 + 13 = 7.
Define each FreshDirect 's Product as N; So N = p = 7.
Define each Aldi (Germany) 's Wine as O; So O = N - p = 7 - 7 = 0.
Define each Aldi (Germany) 's Product as E; So E = O = 0.
Define each Gated Community 's Aldi (Germany) as i; So i = 14 * O = 14 * 0 = 0.
Define each Gated Community 's Product as r; r = i * E = 0 * 0 = 0.
Define each Learning Hub 's Aldi (Germany) as M; So M = r + E = 0 + 0 = 0.
